Wash and dry produce.

Trim and dice @zucchini{1}(trimmed and diced into ¼-inch pieces). Peel and
finely chop @garlic{2%cloves}(peeled and finely chopped). Finely dice
@tomato{1}(finely diced). Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed and
thinly sliced, separating whites from greens). Zest and quarter
@lemon{1}(zested and quartered).

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat.
Add zucchini; season with half the garlic, @salt{1%tsp}, and @black pepper{1%tsp}.
Cook, stirring frequently, until browned and tender, ~{4-7%minutes}.

Turn off heat. Transfer to a #plate{}; cover with #foil{} to keep warm. Wipe
out pan.

While zucchini cooks, melt @butter{1%tbsp} in a small #pot over medium-high
heat. Add @Israeli couscous{3/4%cup} and remaining garlic; cook, stirring,
until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in ¾ cup water and a big pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then cover and
reduce to a low simmer. Cook until couscous is tender, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Drain any excess water if necessary. Keep covered off heat until ready to use
in Step 6.

Pat chicken dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with
@dried thyme{1%tsp}, salt, and pepper.

> Originally pan-seared chicken - swap in @chicken stock concentrate{2}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for zucchini over medium-high heat. Add
chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{5-7%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat. Transfer chicken to a #cutting board{}; tent with foil to keep
warm. Let pan cool for ~{1-2%minutes}.

Swap in @salmon{10%oz} for chicken. Cook (skin sides down) until skin is crisp,
~{5-7%minutes}, then flip and cook until cooked through, ~{1-2%minutes} more.
Transfer to a plate to rest.

Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in same pan over medium heat. Add tomato and scallion
whites; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until
slightly softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{2} and ¼ cup water. Cook, stirring
occasionally, until slightly reduced, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove pan from heat. Whisk in @cream cheese{2%tbsp} until melted and
combined. Season with salt and pepper.

Slice chicken crosswise.

To pot with couscous, stir in zucchini, scallion greens, and lemon zest. Stir
in a squeeze of lemon juice to taste. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

Divide zucchini couscous between plates. Top with chicken; drizzle with tomato
cream sauce. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.

Serve salmon atop zucchini couscous (no need to slice!).